South Africa stands to lose out economically should the Iranians decide to escalate the impasse between itself and the United States, possibly sending crude oil prices sky-rocketing. This according to experts, who have warned that while the killing of Iranian general Qasem Soleimani last week could increase the scourge of insurgency by Islamic extremists in Africa, the direct knock-on effect on South Africa was more likely to be a devastating economic downfall. Institute of Security Studies chief executive officer Jakkie Cilliers said that at stake was more than just the financial interests South Africa had in both countries. Should the...